<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM3.3.6">
<l>eyya<supplied>c</supplied>ci taintati laṅkai malaṅkava rumaḻai kāppāṉ</l>
<l>uyya<supplied>p</supplied>pa ruvarai tāṅki yānirai kāttāṉeṉ ṟētti</l>
<l>vaiyatteva rumvaṇaṅ kava ṇaṅkeḻu māmalai pōlē</l>
<l>teyva<supplied>p</supplied>puḷ ḷēṟiva ruvāṉ cittira kūṭattuḷ ḷāṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>He who appeared riding a divine bird, like a dark mountain</l>
<l rend="indent">from which a deity rises,</l>
<l>As everyone on earth bowed, praising [him], saying, “ Lanka perished</l>
<l rend="indent">when he shot [arrows];</l>
<l>Supporting a huge mountain to guard against the rains which came</l>
<l rend="indent">so [the land] shook,</l>
<l>He protected the cowherd so [they] survived,”</l>
<l rend="indent">he is the one present in Citrakūṭam.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
